Product Information
Bushnell #: 321040T UPC #: REDACTED45
Bushnell Elite 3200 Rifle Scopes feature resettable fingertip adjustments for windage and elevation with repeatable audible clicks. They also feature 1-piece hammer forged aluminum titanium alloy tubes and multi-coated lenses that have been treated with Bushnell's Rainguard coating. This scope features 1/10 milliradian (MIL) windage and elevation turrets and a Mil-dot reticle; this is also known as MIL/MIL. The combination of these two features enables the shooter to make quick and precise corrections. By using the Mil-dot reticle to measure how far off the shot is in MILs, each dot is 1 MIL apart, the shooter does not need to convert milliradians to minutes of angle in order to correct the point of aim. With traditional 1/4 MOA turrets, if the point of impact is measured to be 1.5 MILs low the shooter needs to convert the MILs to MOA and then adjust the turrets which can be confusing. With a MIL/MIL rifle scope if the shot is 1.5 mils low then the shooter simply turns the turret 1.5 mils or 15 clicks. The mil-dot reticle can also be used to determine how far away an object of known size is.
